==English==

===Etymology===
From {{F.}} ''[[accompagnement]]''.

===Pronunciation===
* {{enPR|ə-kŭmʹpə-nē-mənt}}, {{IPA|/əˈkʌmpənimənt/}}, {{SAMPA|/@"kVmp@nim@nt/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# That which gives support or adds to the background in music, or adds for ornamentation.
# That which accompanies; something that attends as a circumstance, or which is added to give greater completeness to the principal thing, or by way of ornament, or for the sake of symmetry.
# {{music}} A part performed by instruments, accompanying another part or parts performed by voices; the subordinate part, or parts, accompanying the voice or a principal instrument; also, the harmony of a figured bass. {{rfd-redundant}}

